item.description:
1. "Labor is the source of wealth and all culture, and since useful labor is possible only in society and through society, the proceeds of labor belong undiminished with equal right to all members of society."
First part of the paragraph: &ldquo;Labor is the source of all wealth and all culture.&rdquo;
Labor is not the source of all wealth. Nature is just as much the source of use values (and it is surely of such that material wealth consists!
